    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-01-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <head>No. 283.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">West</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-01-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 18, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 15th instant in relation to the action which Her Majesty’s
                    Government has taken with reference to the decree of the Venezuelan Government
                        <pb facs="0563" n="493" xml:id="pg_493"/> requiring ships’ papers to be
                    deposited with the port officers, and to inform you that the American minister
                    at Caracas has been advised that Her Majesty’s minister at that capital will act
                    in concert with him in the matter.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN DAVIS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
